                            <comment id="14327794" author="tilman" created="Thu, 19 Feb 2015 17:51:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;After a lot of unsuccessful debugging, I had a look at the code of PDF.js&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/mozilla/pdf.js/blob/c0d17013a28ee7aa048831560b6494a26c52360c/src/core/font_renderer.js&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/mozilla/pdf.js/blob/c0d17013a28ee7aa048831560b6494a26c52360c/src/core/font_renderer.js&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and saw this seemingly weird code:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; glyphIndex = (code[i + 2] &amp;lt;&amp;lt; 8) | code[i + 3];
i += 4;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; arg1, arg2;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; ((flags &amp;amp; 0x01)) {
arg1 = ((code[i] &amp;lt;&amp;lt; 24) | (code[i + 1] &amp;lt;&amp;lt; 16)) &amp;gt;&amp;gt; 16;
arg2 = ((code[i + 2] &amp;lt;&amp;lt; 24) | (code[i + 3] &amp;lt;&amp;lt; 16)) &amp;gt;&amp;gt; 16;
i += 4;
} &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; {
arg1 = code[i++]; arg2 = code[i++];
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Why would they do this 16-rshift at that place and not elsewhere? To keep the sign.&lt;/p&gt;

